    "A hierarchy measure based on the local clustering coefficient 28 was applied for each network layer to calculate the hierarchy, which was successfully applied in other research 29.",
    "Hierarchies are more difficult to form in sparse networks 30 and density related to the spread dynamics of information at network 31 and local level 32.",
    "Among the network-level indicators, we counted the density of each network layer.",
    "Local and global overlapping edge dimensions related to appreciation and trust.",
    "Sympathy factors alongside communication relations indicate deeper relational dimensions 14."
